{
  "stem": "1895.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] After that, we spent our days in bunkers or we spent our days with our face in the dirt that I remember.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there were seven days of constant bombardment, either by Stukas, low-level, low-flying fighter bombers, or the heavy Heinkels that dropped bombs on us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we also heard the drone of planes overhead going on the way to Warsaw, to bomb Warsaw, which they leveled in those days.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I only mention that because the Germans have a habit of reminding us that we bombed Dresden, you know, that we bombed Dresden.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And-- and every time I read about their complaints about our bombing Dresden, I always think of the Stukas coming down and killing that poor milkman with his children and the cows.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And so that was that we had seven days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "On a Friday of the same week, a plane flew over-- overhead, over the city.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it left a-- a mark, which evidently was the sign to the ground troops that the city is empty, and it is ready to be entered.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And after about a half hour, I heard a mighty roar coming in from the western side of the city.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we knew that the Germans were entering the city.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And so I overcame my fright, all my emotions.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And as a curious child, I ran to the road that I knew the Germans were coming in from.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And so I got there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I had to hold my hands over my head like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I watched a whole array of this great German might, tank after tank after tank with these tankers in their goggles, you know, with the-- with this tremendous might, with the long guns on their tanks.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And that made a tremendous impression on me.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
